      <profileDesc>
         <abstract><p><bibl><ptr target="bm:Marrassini2007EAEKiros"/><citedRange unit="page">79–81</citedRange>
         </bibl> refers to this version of the Vita of Kiros as the text of “type 1”, most commonly spread and
            contained in many manuscripts. It is different from the Vita of “type 2” which is
            attested in a few manuscripts only. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Marrassini2004Kiros"/><citedRange unit="page">83</citedRange>
            </bibl> distinguishes two kinds of type 1 Vita of Kiros: “long” and “short”. He points out that they do
            not differ as to their substance — that is, they encompass exactly the same episodes — but as to their form. 
            To be more precise, the “short” gadl lacks some phrases and adjectives present in the “long” one.
         </p>
         </abstract>
